titles.title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (H.R. 1296) to provide for the administration of certain Presidio properties at minimal cost to the Federal taxpayer.

action.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 104-842, by Ms. Greene (UT).

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 1296. All points of order against the conference report and against its consideration are waived. The conference report shall be considered as read when called up for consideration.

calendar.text: Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 284.

bill.summary: 9/25/1996--Introduced. Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 1296 (administration of Presidio properties).
